1
00:00:00,242 --> 00:00:02,054
JUGHEAD: <i>Previously on</i> Riverdale...

2
00:00:02,079 --> 00:00:03,701
<i>This story is about a town,</i>

3
00:00:03,703 --> 00:00:06,237
<i>once wholesome and innocent,
now forever changed</i>

4
00:00:06,239 --> 00:00:09,740
<i>by the mysterious death of Jason
Blossom on the 4th of July.</i>

5
00:00:09,742 --> 00:00:12,109
- Can we talk, Ms. Grundy?
- About what?

6
00:00:12,111 --> 00:00:14,078
ARCHIE: <i>You're the music eacher,
can we talk about music?</i>

7
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:15,412
(GUNSHOT IN DISTANCE)

8
00:00:15,414 --> 00:00:17,681
We heard what we heard and
afterwards we didn't do anything.

9
00:00:17,683 --> 00:00:22,419
How would we explain why we were
together at 6:00 a.m. on the 4th of July?

10
00:00:22,421 --> 00:00:23,721
HERMIONE: Hello, Fred.

11
00:00:23,723 --> 00:00:25,456
- Can I get you anything?
- A job.

12
00:00:25,458 --> 00:00:27,958
I can't very well have
the wife of Hiram LodgLo

13
00:00:27,960 --> 00:00:29,894
on trial for fraud and embezzlement,

14
00:00:29,896 --> 00:00:31,295
balancing my books.

15
00:00:31,320 --> 00:00:33,564
KEVIN: Betty and Archie are endgame.

16
00:00:33,566 --> 00:00:36,834
BETTY: <i>I'm not gonna ask what you
did with Veronica at Cheryl's.</i>

17
00:00:36,836 --> 00:00:40,170
I'm asking you now, right
now, if you love me, Archie.

18
00:00:40,172 --> 00:00:42,239
ARCHIE: I can't give
you the answer you want.

19
00:00:43,476 --> 00:00:45,276
Oh, my God, it's Jason.

20
00:00:46,351 --> 00:00:47,617
He was shot.

21
00:00:51,183 --> 00:00:54,318
JUGHEAD: <i>I think many of
us, maybe the entire town,</i>

22
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:59,924
<i>had been hoping against hope that somehow
Jason Blossom hadn't drowned on July 4th.</i>

23
00:01:00,758 --> 00:01:02,925
<i>That we'd come to school Monday morning,</i>

24
00:01:02,950 --> 00:01:05,663
<i>and there Jason would be.</i>

25
00:01:07,473 --> 00:01:10,640
<i>Or that we'd see him and
Cheryl in a booth at Pop's.</i>

26
00:01:11,362 --> 00:01:14,405
<i>But that was before the
undeniable, irrevocable fact</i>

27
00:01:14,407 --> 00:01:16,774
<i>of his bloated, water-logged body,</i>

28
00:01:16,776 --> 00:01:19,810
<i>a corpse with a bullet
hole in its forehead,</i>

29
00:01:19,812 --> 00:01:21,946
<i>and terrible secrets that
could only be revealed</i>

30
00:01:21,948 --> 00:01:25,516
<i>by the cold, steel blade of
a coroner's autopsy scalpel,</i>

31
00:01:25,518 --> 00:01:29,486
<i>or the telltale beating
of a guilty heart.</i>

32
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:38,586
(GUNSHOT IN DISTANCE)

33
00:01:44,565 --> 00:01:46,247
_

34
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:47,671
(PHONE VIBRATES)

35
00:01:54,836 --> 00:01:57,196
_

36
00:01:58,951 --> 00:02:00,317
(SIGHS)

37
00:02:03,329 --> 00:02:06,696
_

38
00:02:20,706 --> 00:02:22,172
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

39
00:02:30,391 --> 00:02:31,590
(KNOCKING)

40
00:02:32,418 --> 00:02:33,884
Archie, what are you doing here?

41
00:02:33,886 --> 00:02:35,719
- It wasn't fireworks, Ms. Grundy.
- You can't be here, Archie.

42
00:02:35,721 --> 00:02:38,355
- On July 4th, it was a gunshot we heard.
- You can't come to my house.

43
00:02:38,357 --> 00:02:40,357
Probably the shot that
killed Jason Blossom.

44
00:02:40,359 --> 00:02:42,760
We know exactly what the police know.

45
00:02:42,762 --> 00:02:44,294
That a gun was fired.

46
00:02:44,296 --> 00:02:46,764
That a boy was shot.
We don't know by whom.

47
00:02:46,766 --> 00:02:49,800
We know when it was fired. That's
something the police still don't know.

48
00:02:49,802 --> 00:02:51,201
(SIGHS) They're performing an autopsy.

49
00:02:51,203 --> 00:02:52,836
We could call them, anonymously.

50
00:02:52,838 --> 00:02:59,476
This is not a negotiation,
Archie. This is our lives.

51
00:02:59,478 --> 00:03:01,512
If anybody knows that we were there,

52
00:03:01,514 --> 00:03:05,683
I could lose my job. You could
be expelled. We could go to jail.

53
00:03:10,149 --> 00:03:11,915
FRED: All right. Here you go, Vegas.

54
00:03:12,992 --> 00:03:14,458
Good boy.

55
00:03:14,827 --> 00:03:15,993
Wow.

56
00:03:16,595 --> 00:03:18,562
- Morning, Dad.
- Hey, bud.

57
00:03:19,291 --> 00:03:21,257
Where'd you sneak off to last night?

58
00:03:21,932 --> 00:03:23,432
You, uh, you heard that?

59
00:03:23,457 --> 00:03:27,004
Son, I've been hearing you sneak
out since you were eight years old

60
00:03:27,006 --> 00:03:28,839
going to Jughead's tree house.

61
00:03:29,761 --> 00:03:32,795
I couldn't sleep. Went for
a jog to tire myself out.

62
00:03:32,820 --> 00:03:35,012
Yeah? Got something on your mind?

63
00:03:37,016 --> 00:03:39,183
- Just all this stuff with Jason.
- Hmm.

64
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:41,420
No more midnight runs
until the police catch

65
00:03:41,445 --> 00:03:43,387
whoever it was that shot that poor kid.

66
00:03:43,389 --> 00:03:45,422
I swear to God, this town.

67
00:03:47,093 --> 00:03:48,158
(KNOCKING)

68
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:50,027
- (DOOR OPENS)
- HAL: Hey, honey?

69
00:03:50,688 --> 00:03:53,564
We just wanted you to know, it's
gonna be a bit of a late night for us.

70
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:56,266
It's going to be a lot
of late nights for us.

71
00:03:56,268 --> 00:03:58,969
I mean, an accidental
drowning, who cares?

72
00:03:58,971 --> 00:04:02,306
But the sociopathic son of the
wealthiest family in town, murdered?

73
00:04:02,308 --> 00:04:05,242
That's a national
obsession waiting to happen.

74
00:04:05,244 --> 00:04:06,710
He's barely in his grave, Alice.

75
00:04:06,712 --> 00:04:09,113
Can you warm up the car,
Hal? I'll be right down.

76
00:04:12,184 --> 00:04:15,452
Betty, you know what
I love most about you?

77
00:04:16,493 --> 00:04:19,193
It's that you always want
to see the good in people.

78
00:04:19,218 --> 00:04:21,225
Even people like Cheryl Blossom

79
00:04:21,227 --> 00:04:23,494
and Veronica Lodge and Archie Andrews.

80
00:04:23,519 --> 00:04:25,996
But when they betrayed you this weekend,

81
00:04:25,998 --> 00:04:28,098
you saw their true colors, didn't you?

82
00:04:28,734 --> 00:04:30,167
I did. I definitely did.

83
00:04:30,169 --> 00:04:32,269
So no backsliding.

84
00:04:32,688 --> 00:04:35,155
No Cheryl. No Veronica and...

85
00:04:35,180 --> 00:04:36,569
No Archie.

86
00:04:36,594 --> 00:04:37,560
(DOORBELL RINGING)

87
00:04:41,547 --> 00:04:43,180
Walk me to school?

88
00:04:45,484 --> 00:04:47,217
I needed time to process.

89
00:04:47,219 --> 00:04:52,122
To separate what my mom wants
from what I want... I think I want.

90
00:04:52,124 --> 00:04:53,323
Which is?

91
00:04:53,348 --> 00:04:56,193
My mom says I should
never speak to you again.

92
00:04:57,196 --> 00:04:58,695
But I...

93
00:04:58,697 --> 00:05:02,833
Even though you don't like me like that,

94
00:05:02,835 --> 00:05:06,503
I still want us to be
friends... Best friends.

95
00:05:06,505 --> 00:05:07,871
You do?

96
00:05:07,896 --> 00:05:08,962
Yeah.

97
00:05:09,749 --> 00:05:12,517
I mean, that's great, Betty. Me, too.

98
00:05:13,045 --> 00:05:15,779
I'd be lying if I said
that it didn't hurt.

99
00:05:15,781 --> 00:05:19,650
And I'm sorry, Betty,
I didn't do it to be a...

100
00:05:20,896 --> 00:05:23,720
I don't know, I just... I thought
it would be better in the long run.

101
00:05:23,722 --> 00:05:25,088
And it will be.

102
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:29,974
Oh, and don't tell my mom
that we're friends again.

103
00:05:40,244 --> 00:05:41,410
Hi.

104
00:05:42,686 --> 00:05:47,077
Do you think I can use Jason Blossom's
death as an excuse to get out of PE?

105
00:05:47,102 --> 00:05:51,767
"Sorry, Coach, I'm just too depressed
and freaked-out right now to do pull-ups."

106
00:05:52,585 --> 00:05:54,685
Don't joke about Jason Blossom.

107
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:55,886
What?

108
00:05:55,911 --> 00:05:59,109
Sardonic humor is just my
way of relating to the world.

109
00:06:01,129 --> 00:06:04,376
(SCOFFS) Look, it's the rich
kids from <i>The Goonies.</i>

110
00:06:06,195 --> 00:06:08,095
All right, I'm out.

111
00:06:12,577 --> 00:06:14,511
Watch it, Wednesday Addams.

112
00:06:14,536 --> 00:06:17,307
KEVIN: Now that romance is off
the table, I'll just say it.

113
00:06:17,309 --> 00:06:19,176
Are we 100% sure that Archie's straight?

114
00:06:19,178 --> 00:06:22,112
Because no straight man has that body.

115
00:06:22,982 --> 00:06:24,948
Speaking of bodies...

116
00:06:25,818 --> 00:06:28,485
Have you recovered from finding Jason's?

117
00:06:28,487 --> 00:06:30,988
It was more traumatizing
having to explain to my dad

118
00:06:30,990 --> 00:06:32,723
what I was doing with
Moose at the river.

119
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:35,359
Yet another perk of
being the sheriff's son.

120
00:06:36,996 --> 00:06:38,762
Oh, my God, those are gorgeous.

121
00:06:38,764 --> 00:06:40,764
Are those for Betty, Mrs. Philips?

122
00:06:41,273 --> 00:06:42,972
That's why I called her.

123
00:06:46,972 --> 00:06:49,907
"Dear Betty, please
forgive me, XOXO, V."

124
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:51,842
Who the hell is "V"?

125
00:06:52,558 --> 00:06:54,157
- Veronica.
- VERONICA: Veronica.

126
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:56,413
The yellow is for friendship.

127
00:06:56,415 --> 00:07:00,417
I also had Magnolia cupcakes
flown in from New York.

128
00:07:00,419 --> 00:07:02,386
Because, as my mom likes to say,

129
00:07:02,388 --> 00:07:05,355
"There's no wrong the
right cupcake can't fix."

130
00:07:06,605 --> 00:07:10,140
Also I... I've booked us for
hers-and-hers mani-pedis at Chez Salon.

131
00:07:11,075 --> 00:07:12,341
Blowouts, too.

132
00:07:12,366 --> 00:07:15,465
I am so, so sorry, Betty.

133
00:07:15,467 --> 00:07:19,503
I don't know what happened to me that
night. It was such a basic bitch move.

134
00:07:19,505 --> 00:07:21,104
It was like I was...

135
00:07:21,129 --> 00:07:22,439
Possessed by...

136
00:07:22,441 --> 00:07:23,874
Madame Satan?

137
00:07:25,170 --> 00:07:27,638
The old Veronica.

138
00:07:30,082 --> 00:07:33,317
And I will never, ever do
anything like that to you again.

139
00:07:33,319 --> 00:07:35,552
I swear on my mother's pearls.

140
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:39,965
Just, can you please
give me one more chance?

141
00:07:42,461 --> 00:07:43,760
Okay.

142
00:07:44,396 --> 00:07:45,662
- What?
- What?

143
00:07:45,664 --> 00:07:47,030
VERONICA: Really?

144
00:07:47,032 --> 00:07:50,320
Awesome. I'll take it
and you won't regret it.

145
00:07:50,345 --> 00:07:51,168
Okay.

146
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:53,203
And I'll bring these to
lunch so we can celebrate!

147
00:07:54,106 --> 00:07:55,839
(BELL RINGING)

148
00:07:59,095 --> 00:08:01,260
It's the path of least resistance, Kev.

149
00:08:02,518 --> 00:08:05,549
A week ago, Veronica
and I weren't friends.

150
00:08:05,551 --> 00:08:09,179
Next week, we'll nod to each other
as we pass in the hall, but that's it.

151
00:08:09,204 --> 00:08:11,488
You know, in two weeks, she
won't even remember my name.

152
00:08:11,490 --> 00:08:14,491
And in three, she'll have latched
he to some other girl to destroy.

153
00:08:16,028 --> 00:08:18,729
WEATHERBEE: <i>Good morning, students.
This is your principal speaking.</i>

154
00:08:18,731 --> 00:08:21,565
There have been many inquiries
about the upcoming pep rally.

155
00:08:21,567 --> 00:08:25,535
So let me state clearly, it
is happening, as scheduled.

156
00:08:26,632 --> 00:08:29,961
Now, on a less felicitous
note, if you could

157
00:08:29,986 --> 00:08:31,632
give your attention to Sheriff Keller.

158
00:08:35,342 --> 00:08:37,408
Most of you already know the details,

159
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:42,886
<i>but your classmate Jason Blossom's
body was found late Saturday night.</i>

160
00:08:42,888 --> 00:08:48,225
<i>So as of the weekend, Jason's death
is now being treated as a homicide.</i>

161
00:08:49,695 --> 00:08:52,829
<i>It is an open and ongoing investigation.</i>

162
00:08:52,831 --> 00:08:56,199
And may I interject,
neither I nor my parents

163
00:08:56,201 --> 00:08:58,035
will rest until Jason's
death is avenged,

164
00:08:58,037 --> 00:09:03,106
and his cold-hearted killer is walking the
green mile to sit in Old Sparky and fry.

165
00:09:03,861 --> 00:09:06,650
I, for one, have my suspicions.
#RiverdaleStrong.

166
00:09:09,931 --> 00:09:11,681
If you know anything

167
00:09:11,683 --> 00:09:15,452
<i>that could help us find and
apprehend Jason's killer,</i>

168
00:09:15,454 --> 00:09:19,289
<i>or anything about what
happened to him on July 4th,</i>

169
00:09:19,291 --> 00:09:23,293
<i>I strongly urge you to
come forward immediately.</i>

170
00:09:23,295 --> 00:09:27,264
You can speak with me
or Principal Weatherbee.

171
00:09:27,266 --> 00:09:29,566
A death like this wounds us all.

172
00:09:29,568 --> 00:09:31,468
<i>Let's not let Jason down.</i>

173
00:09:35,274 --> 00:09:36,673
JUGHEAD: Archie.

174
00:09:38,944 --> 00:09:44,038
Weirdest thing. This summer, we
were supposed to go on a road trip

175
00:09:44,063 --> 00:09:47,184
over July 4th weekend...

176
00:09:47,186 --> 00:09:51,154
Which you bailed on at the last minute.

177
00:09:53,859 --> 00:09:56,226
Is there something
you wanna tell me, pal?

178
00:09:59,952 --> 00:10:03,382
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

179
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:09,066
(BELL RINGING)

180
00:10:13,939 --> 00:10:15,272
We were wondering, Cheryl.

181
00:10:15,274 --> 00:10:17,674
Back in July, you told the
po-po that Jason drowned.

182
00:10:17,676 --> 00:10:21,411
Yet, we come to find out
that Jason didn't drown.

183
00:10:21,785 --> 00:10:25,115
He was shot. That's
slightly suspicious, no?

184
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:28,919
Are you living mannequins suggesting I had
something to do with my brother's death?

185
00:10:28,921 --> 00:10:31,621
We're just curious. What do
the police think happened?

186
00:10:31,623 --> 00:10:35,325
I'll tell you what I told them, which
is that Jason did fall into the water.

187
00:10:35,327 --> 00:10:39,429
We both did. I made it
to the shore. He didn't.

188
00:10:39,431 --> 00:10:41,331
Maybe he made it to
the other side of the

189
00:10:41,356 --> 00:10:43,367
river and someone shot him
there. Who knows?

190
00:10:43,369 --> 00:10:46,403
Seats, everyone. Pair off,
gloves on, scalpels up.

191
00:10:46,405 --> 00:10:47,313
Can I be with Cheryl?

192
00:10:47,338 --> 00:10:48,971
And I wanna be with Betty.

193
00:10:49,485 --> 00:10:51,975
Oh, uh, I was thinking
I'd partner with Kevin.

194
00:10:51,977 --> 00:10:55,679
Actually, uh, Keller's
with me. We, like, talked.

195
00:10:55,704 --> 00:10:57,170
Oh, God.

196
00:11:00,319 --> 00:11:03,487
- Once again, fate throws us together.
- Hmm.

197
00:11:03,512 --> 00:11:06,890
So... Saturday night.

198
00:11:06,892 --> 00:11:09,126
Listen, Moose, you're hot. Yes.

199
00:11:09,128 --> 00:11:11,862
My type? Definitely.

200
00:11:11,887 --> 00:11:14,531
But you've got more demons
than <i>The Exorcist.</i>

201
00:11:14,533 --> 00:11:16,633
We're all on the spectrum,
but my gay-o-meter

202
00:11:16,635 --> 00:11:19,636
says you should stick with
what you know best... Girls.

203
00:11:19,661 --> 00:11:22,305
Cheryl, we haven't
talked since the summer.

204
00:11:22,307 --> 00:11:24,674
I just want to say, I'm really
sorry about your brother.

205
00:11:24,676 --> 00:11:26,209
Jason was the best.

206
00:11:26,234 --> 00:11:28,278
If I can do anything to help.

207
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:30,981
That's sweet, Archie, but unless
you were at Sweetwater River

208
00:11:30,983 --> 00:11:32,682
and know who shot Jason...

209
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:45,128
Do, uh, do you know if
the police have any leads?

210
00:11:45,153 --> 00:11:49,900
What? No, you ghoul. But
it's only a matter of time.

211
00:11:49,902 --> 00:11:53,003
And my twintuition is telling
me it's someone we all know.

212
00:11:54,095 --> 00:11:57,307
Right. Well, I'm not great at science,

213
00:11:57,309 --> 00:11:59,876
but I can take point on this
if it's too weird for you.

214
00:12:00,266 --> 00:12:01,599
Weird, why?

215
00:12:02,463 --> 00:12:06,650
Oh, you mean because my brother
is being dissected with a blade,

216
00:12:06,652 --> 00:12:09,820
just like this one,
possibly at this very moment?

217
00:12:09,822 --> 00:12:12,089
Don't worry, I'm fine.

218
00:12:12,629 --> 00:12:15,897
In fact, I'm amazing.

219
00:12:16,728 --> 00:12:21,131
Every corpse has as tale to
tell. Step closer to the body.

220
00:12:21,133 --> 00:12:26,103
There are several morbid details you
should find relevant to your article.

221
00:12:26,940 --> 00:12:29,106
What details, Dr. Curdle?

222
00:12:29,131 --> 00:12:31,272
What sticks out to you?

223
00:12:31,297 --> 00:12:34,678
The marbling of the veins.
Signs of scavenger activity.

224
00:12:35,313 --> 00:12:37,547
Ligature marks on both wrists.

225
00:12:37,549 --> 00:12:41,251
And a hint of
cryo-necrotic preservation.

226
00:12:45,290 --> 00:12:47,257
Small bills, right?

227
00:12:52,061 --> 00:12:54,464
So, what did Moose want?

228
00:12:54,466 --> 00:12:56,766
Oh, my God, I don't even think he knows.

229
00:12:56,768 --> 00:12:59,636
I mean, I am devastatingly
handsome in that classic,

230
00:12:59,638 --> 00:13:01,805
pre-accident Montgomery
Clift kind of way,

231
00:13:01,807 --> 00:13:06,209
and sexuality is fluid, but can someone
named Moose actually be that fluid?

232
00:13:06,211 --> 00:13:08,678
- (LAUGHS)
- Okay, well, I ship it.

233
00:13:08,680 --> 00:13:11,848
Well, of course you would. You're
a big city girl with loose morals.

234
00:13:13,886 --> 00:13:16,920
I just meant that Moose has
an official girlfriend, Midge.

235
00:13:17,684 --> 00:13:19,979
Anyway, it's terrible
to say, but part of me

