251
00:14:20,219 --> 00:14:21,785
(CLAPPING)

252
00:14:24,623 --> 00:14:25,822
Betty?

253
00:14:27,609 --> 00:14:29,076
You okay?

254
00:14:30,521 --> 00:14:31,732
(CHUCKLES)

255
00:14:32,146 --> 00:14:34,431
I'm supposed to say, "Yes."

256
00:14:35,573 --> 00:14:38,732
That's what the nice
girl always says, but...

257
00:14:38,757 --> 00:14:40,375
No, I'm not.

258
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:44,007
I want to be. I thought I could
be. But it's too much, too fast.

259
00:14:44,009 --> 00:14:46,042
- Archie...
- Betty.

260
00:14:46,044 --> 00:14:47,477
Betty, wait.

261
00:14:52,651 --> 00:14:56,086
- Betty, wait. Come on. Listen to me.
- No.

262
00:14:56,088 --> 00:15:01,124
No, when... When I think, Archie, of
where I feel safest and most myself,

263
00:15:01,126 --> 00:15:03,460
- I think of us, in a booth, at Pop's...
- Me, too.

264
00:15:03,462 --> 00:15:04,694
But that's not true anymore.

265
00:15:05,748 --> 00:15:08,749
I thought I could pretend this
weekend didn't happen, but...

266
00:15:10,272 --> 00:15:12,068
"I can't give you the answer you want."

267
00:15:12,070 --> 00:15:13,270
That's what you said to me.

268
00:15:13,272 --> 00:15:15,238
And that's how I feel
right now, I'm sorry.

269
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:16,506
Betty.

270
00:15:16,508 --> 00:15:18,041
Mr. Andrews.

271
00:15:18,777 --> 00:15:20,877
If we could have a word in private.

272
00:15:23,079 --> 00:15:25,947
You're in a very good place
right now, Mr. Andrews.

273
00:15:27,319 --> 00:15:30,220
Varsity football, AP music tutorials.

274
00:15:32,161 --> 00:15:34,795
This morning, in the hallway,
you wouldn't meet my eyes.

275
00:15:35,961 --> 00:15:37,060
Why?

276
00:15:37,062 --> 00:15:38,828
I was distracted. I wasn't feeling well.

277
00:15:38,830 --> 00:15:40,664
Archie...

278
00:15:41,389 --> 00:15:44,057
If there's something you
want to get off your chest,

279
00:15:44,082 --> 00:15:48,989
perhaps about Jason,
now would be the time.

280
00:15:53,945 --> 00:15:56,313
Weatherbee just asked me if
I knew anything about Jason.

281
00:15:57,082 --> 00:15:58,448
And?

282
00:15:58,473 --> 00:16:00,047
What did you say?

283
00:16:00,072 --> 00:16:01,985
Nothing. That I didn't.

284
00:16:01,987 --> 00:16:05,588
But he said that if I did, I shouldn't be
scared, and he'd make sure I was okay.

285
00:16:05,590 --> 00:16:07,657
Of course he would, you're his student.

286
00:16:09,328 --> 00:16:11,461
Is this...

287
00:16:11,963 --> 00:16:13,897
How you feel about me?

288
00:16:13,899 --> 00:16:15,465
Is it real?

289
00:16:18,904 --> 00:16:21,938
Because if it's not, then I
don't know what I'm protecting.

290
00:16:25,644 --> 00:16:27,210
It is.

291
00:16:30,382 --> 00:16:31,715
It is real.

292
00:16:33,739 --> 00:16:37,920
Maybe it's not right, but it's real.

293
00:16:38,990 --> 00:16:41,491
Which is why...

294
00:16:42,127 --> 00:16:44,294
We... You...

295
00:16:45,397 --> 00:16:47,497
Can't go to Weatherbee.

296
00:16:47,499 --> 00:16:49,866
If you do that,

297
00:16:49,868 --> 00:16:51,901
we will never see each other again.

298
00:16:59,077 --> 00:17:01,344
Archie,

299
