<i>♪ Go and get it, get it</i>

304
00:17:35,955 --> 00:17:36,987
<i>♪ Let's go, let's go</i>

305
00:17:36,989 --> 00:17:38,255
<i>♪ Go and get it, get it</i>

306
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:39,557
(MUSIC STOPS)

307
00:17:39,559 --> 00:17:40,724
Stand down, Vixens.

308
00:17:40,749 --> 00:17:42,183
And listen up.

309
00:17:43,396 --> 00:17:46,497
The weather's predicting a
downpour the night of the rally,

310
00:17:46,499 --> 00:17:49,166
but already, you're
raining on my parade.

311
00:17:49,168 --> 00:17:52,036
With Jason so present in
our collective consciousness,

312
00:17:52,038 --> 00:17:54,672
all eyes will be on me.

313
00:17:54,674 --> 00:17:57,508
Will this beautiful,
exotic, hothouse flower

314
00:17:57,510 --> 00:17:59,143
drown under the town's scrutiny,

315
00:17:59,145 --> 00:18:01,512
or be swamped by her emotions?

316
00:18:02,315 --> 00:18:04,949
The answer, ladies, is "no" and "no."

317
00:18:04,951 --> 00:18:08,519
That said, I need star power.

318
00:18:09,710 --> 00:18:11,355
I need the Pussycats.

319
00:18:11,357 --> 00:18:14,024
Stay loose and limber,
ladies, while I make a call.

320
00:18:19,899 --> 00:18:23,200
After this practice, I'll
totally need a pedicure. You?

321
00:18:25,152 --> 00:18:26,551
I'll have homework.

322
00:18:30,843 --> 00:18:33,310
I know everyone grieves differently,

323
00:18:33,312 --> 00:18:35,613
but Cheryl's hosting a pep
rally to cope with her loss.

324
00:18:35,615 --> 00:18:38,516
That's either brilliant,
or psychotic, or both.

325
00:18:38,518 --> 00:18:42,219
Yeah, well, at least Cheryl's
not putting on an act.

326
00:18:42,221 --> 00:18:45,556
Pretending she's a butterfly
when really she's a wasp.

327
00:18:50,029 --> 00:18:53,597
For the record, the only reason I
went into that closet with Archie

328
00:18:53,599 --> 00:18:55,299
was so that Cheryl wouldn't.

329
00:18:55,301 --> 00:18:58,035
- Oh, so you did it to protect me?
- Damn straight.

330
00:18:58,037 --> 00:19:01,238
Okay, so nothing happened between
you and Archie in the closet, then?

331
00:19:01,928 --> 00:19:03,620
Yeah, that's what I thought.

332
00:19:03,644 --> 00:19:06,577
You know, Archie and
I were fine before you got here.

333
00:19:06,579 --> 00:19:08,212
If by, fine,

334
00:19:08,214 --> 00:19:11,682
you mean he was oblivious and you were
pining after him in quiet desperation.

335
00:19:11,684 --> 00:19:13,384
We were friends, at least.

336
00:19:13,386 --> 00:19:16,253
You were walking on emotional eggshells
around him, scared to tell him the truth.

337
00:19:16,255 --> 00:19:17,421
Okay, you don't know me, Veronica.

338
00:19:17,423 --> 00:19:19,089
It is not my fault he doesn't like you.

339
00:19:22,328 --> 00:19:24,695
(SIGHS) If that's what you're thinking.

340
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:27,398
It's not anyone's fault.
It's not even stupid Archie's.

341
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:29,166
's just how it is.

342
00:19:29,168 --> 00:19:32,336
Most of the time the people
we like don't like us back.

343
00:19:33,102 --> 00:19:35,462
Romeo and Juliet are the
exception, not the rule.

344
00:19:36,909 --> 00:19:38,509
Look...

345
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:41,478
Never speak to me again. If that's
what you want, I'll accept that.

346
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:43,781
But what, exactly, did Archie do wrong?

347
00:19:43,783 --> 00:19:46,383
- Are you seriously taking his side?
- No, I'm not taking any...

348
00:19:46,385 --> 00:19:48,252
And this is your way of trying
to be friends with me again?

349
00:19:48,254 --> 00:19:51,288
The Pussycats are in. Oh,
sorry, ladies, am I interrupting?

350
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:52,623
- As a matter of fact...
- No, you're not.

351
00:19:52,625 --> 00:19:55,292
Actually, I was about to
come and find you, Cheryl.

352
00:19:55,294 --> 00:19:58,195
I have a gift certificate
for hers-and-hers mani-pedis

353
00:19:58,197 --> 00:19:59,830
and blowouts at Chez Salon.

354
00:19:59,832 --> 00:20:01,365
- Do you want to come with me?
- Don't do this.

355
00:20:01,367 --> 00:20:02,733
Butt out, closet monster.

356
00:20:02,735 --> 00:20:05,431
You have forfeited your right
to take the high and mighty road.

357
00:20:06,372 --> 00:20:08,939
As <i>pour moi,</i> Betty, but of course.

358
00:20:08,964 --> 00:20:10,774
I never say no to a pedi.

359
00:20:10,776 --> 00:20:13,210
And I was just about to
suggest the same thing.

360
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:15,546
Can I steal her for a second?

361
00:20:28,027 --> 00:20:29,193
(SIGHS)

362
00:20:29,776 --> 00:20:32,824
You're doing great, Mom.
Better than me this week.

363
00:20:33,511 --> 00:20:36,166
Yeah, we're surviving,
Ronnie, by our wits,

364
00:20:36,168 --> 00:20:38,402
because that's what we Lodge women do.

365
00:20:39,438 --> 00:20:41,171
If Dad could see us now.

366
00:20:41,173 --> 00:20:44,889
He'd say you look stunning
in that new uniform.

367
00:20:44,914 --> 00:20:48,479
I'm going for this Joan Crawford,
Mildred Pierce thing. Is it working?

368
00:20:48,481 --> 00:20:50,180
(CHUCKLES) Definitely.

369
00:20:50,182 --> 00:20:51,448
(BELLS JINGLING)

370
00:20:56,155 --> 00:20:57,321
Hi.

371
00:20:57,757 --> 00:20:58,922
Hi.

372
00:20:59,510 --> 00:21:01,635
And who might this heartbreaker be?

373
00:21:02,995 --> 00:21:05,129
I'm picking up an order for Andrews.

374
00:21:05,131 --> 00:21:06,764
Oh, you're Fred's son?

375
00:21:07,733 --> 00:21:09,566
You're as handsome as your father was.

376
00:21:09,568 --> 00:21:11,535
VERONICA: I'll see you at home, Mom.

377
00:21:11,537 --> 00:21:14,938
Uh, wait. I'm sure Archie
would happily escort you.

378
00:21:19,242 --> 00:21:21,642
Is, uh, Betty still mad at you?

379
00:21:22,515 --> 00:21:24,314
We're back to no texting.

380
00:21:24,316 --> 00:21:25,779
What about you?

381
00:21:25,804 --> 00:21:28,610
I'm back to being the
shallow, toxic, rich

382
00:21:28,635 --> 00:21:31,245
bitch who ruins
everything in her path.

383
00:21:31,749 --> 00:21:34,825
Which is unfortunate, because
even though I only just met Betty,

384
00:21:34,827 --> 00:21:37,528
it really felt like we were
meant to be best friends.

385
00:21:37,530 --> 00:21:41,765
Like... Like it was
our destiny, and now...

386
00:21:42,683 --> 00:21:46,370
(SIGHS) It's like there was this train
that was heading to the rest of my life

387
00:21:46,372 --> 00:21:49,006
and I just missed it.

388
00:21:49,442 --> 00:21:50,641
(CHUCKLES)

389
00:21:52,178 --> 00:21:55,379
Betty and I have been next-door
neighbors since we were four.

390
00:21:55,791 --> 00:21:59,016
We've always gone to the same
school, been in the same class.

391
00:21:59,837 --> 00:22:02,486
I remember in the second grade,

392
00:22:02,488 --> 00:22:04,788
I was having trouble reading,
and my teacher, Mrs. Gribrock,

393
00:22:04,790 --> 00:22:08,292
told my mom and dad that I should
stay back a year, to get caught up.

394
00:22:09,086 --> 00:22:12,730
Betty was so against us
not being in the same grade

395
00:22:12,732 --> 00:22:15,632
that she took it upon herself
to tutor me every single day.

396
00:22:16,302 --> 00:22:18,335
- In the second grade?
- Yeah.

397
00:22:18,360 --> 00:22:21,705
Anyway, when I passed, thanks to Betty,

398
00:22:21,707 --> 00:22:25,042
I kissed her and I
asked her to marry me.

399
00:22:26,278 --> 00:22:29,079
She was like, "Oh, little
Archie, we're too young."

400
00:22:29,081 --> 00:22:31,281
"Ask me when we're 18 and I'll say yes."

401
00:22:31,283 --> 00:22:32,583
Wow.

402
00:22:35,855 --> 00:22:37,387
I hate that I hurt her.

403
00:22:39,125 --> 00:22:42,526
Give her time, Archie.
That's all you can do.

404
00:22:44,430 --> 00:22:48,232
And don't despair. I don't think
your story with Betty is over.

405
00:22:52,304 --> 00:22:54,505
(DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

406
00:22:57,777 --> 00:22:59,409
Your room's so sweet.

407
00:23:01,514 --> 00:23:05,048
It's too pink. It doesn't
feel right anymore.

408
00:23:05,050 --> 00:23:07,317
No, I like how girly it is.

409
00:23:08,087 --> 00:23:09,620
Mine is, too.

410
00:23:09,622 --> 00:23:11,421
You should come over
and see it sometime.

411
00:23:11,423 --> 00:23:13,690
But, just you, not Veronica.

412
00:23:15,327 --> 00:23:18,923
I mean, she must be evil incarnate if
even you won't have her as a friend.

413
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:24,201
And on the subject of being friends,

414
00:23:25,371 --> 00:23:27,491
Betty, I'm sorry I've been
such a witchy-witch to you.

415
00:23:29,175 --> 00:23:31,341
After Polly and Jason's epic demise

416
