How, uh, how is Polly?

422
00:23:47,478 --> 00:23:49,560
Is she still in that group home?

423
00:23:49,562 --> 00:23:52,349
Do you think she knows what happened
to Jason, that he was murdered?

424
00:23:53,299 --> 00:23:56,333
I... I'm not sure.

425
00:23:56,335 --> 00:23:57,901
What do you think
went down between them?

426
00:23:57,903 --> 00:23:58,969
I don't know...

427
00:23:58,971 --> 00:24:00,270
What do your parents say?

428
00:24:00,272 --> 00:24:02,105
About Jason and Polly?

429
00:24:02,541 --> 00:24:04,074
Not a lot.

430
00:24:04,099 --> 00:24:05,489
Same.

431
00:24:05,514 --> 00:24:07,810
I keep thinking that maybe
Jason said something

432
00:24:07,835 --> 00:24:09,580
to her or she said something to him.

433
00:24:09,582 --> 00:24:12,649
I mean, didn't they have a
big fight this summer, or...

434
00:24:12,651 --> 00:24:15,552
Why are you asking me so
many questions about Polly?

435
00:24:19,792 --> 00:24:20,958
Cheryl?

436
00:24:21,747 --> 00:24:24,161
Because, you dumb cow,
someone shot my brother

437
00:24:24,163 --> 00:24:26,864
and I think it was your
crazy, tweaked-out sister.

438
00:24:30,135 --> 00:24:31,301
(SIGHS)

439
00:24:40,713 --> 00:24:42,579
Get out of my house.

440
00:24:43,115 --> 00:24:44,214
Not until you tell me...

441
00:24:44,216 --> 00:24:47,718
Cheryl, get the hell out of
my house before I kill you.

442
00:24:53,952 --> 00:24:55,117
(SIGHS)

443
00:24:56,428 --> 00:24:58,695
Jug. What's up?

444
00:25:00,362 --> 00:25:02,495
What's up is I saw you, Archie.

445
00:25:03,869 --> 00:25:05,736
In the music room. With Ms. Grundy.

446
00:25:05,738 --> 00:25:07,371
Keep your voice down, my dad's inside.

447
00:25:07,373 --> 00:25:10,173
I'm trying to help you, dude.

448
00:25:10,198 --> 00:25:12,263
I'm trying to be your friend here.

449
00:25:12,288 --> 00:25:13,687
Even though we're not anymore.

450
00:25:14,780 --> 00:25:16,213
How long?

451
00:25:16,238 --> 00:25:17,651
You and Grundy?

452
00:25:20,019 --> 00:25:21,351
Since the summer.

453
00:25:23,355 --> 00:25:24,621
I like her.

454
00:25:24,623 --> 00:25:25,889
(SCOFFS)

455
00:25:27,826 --> 00:25:30,836
So I'm guessing she's the reason
you've been acting weird since summer?

456
00:25:31,730 --> 00:25:33,063
One of them.

457
00:25:33,065 --> 00:25:35,866
"One of them." There's more?

458
00:25:38,404 --> 00:25:40,671
We were at Sweetwater River on July 4th.

459
00:25:44,310 --> 00:25:46,710
We heard a gunshot. The gunshot.

460
00:25:46,712 --> 00:25:49,646
- Dude, you have to tell somebody.
- I can't.

461
00:25:50,649 --> 00:25:52,683
Neither can you. If people
find out about Grundy...

462
00:25:52,685 --> 00:25:54,384
A kid is dead, Archie!

463
00:25:55,321 --> 00:25:57,888
And you're worried about
some... Some cougar?

464
00:25:57,890 --> 00:25:59,189
Don't call her that.

465
00:25:59,191 --> 00:26:01,358
Okay, she's not like
that, she cares about me.

466
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:02,926
Stab in the dark.

467
00:26:02,928 --> 00:26:05,796
I'm guessing she cares
more about herself.

468
00:26:05,798 --> 00:26:07,184
She's the one who's telling you

469
00:26:07,209 --> 00:26:08,808
not to say anything, right?

470
00:26:10,936 --> 00:26:14,571
Look, I saw you guys.
She's messing with you, man.

471
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:16,173
And she's messing with your mind...

472
00:26:16,175 --> 00:26:18,108
What the hell do you
know about it, Jughead?

473
00:26:18,110 --> 00:26:19,810
Or about me, even?

474
00:26:21,613 --> 00:26:22,779
Nothing.

475
00:26:23,682 --> 00:26:26,149
But I used to know this guy once.

476
00:26:26,552 --> 00:26:27,584
Archie Andrews.

477
00:26:28,887 --> 00:26:30,954
He wasn't perfect but...

478
00:26:31,390 --> 00:26:32,756
(SIGHS)

479
00:26:32,781 --> 00:26:35,559
He always tried to do
the right thing, at least.

480
00:26:35,561 --> 00:26:37,094
Jug.

481
00:26:38,130 --> 00:26:40,397
- (SIGHS)
- If you tell anyone about this...

